# Leaflet Map Conventions

## Setup

- Use `react-leaflet` components: `MapContainer`, `TileLayer`, `Marker`, `Popup`
- Tile provider: CARTO dark tiles (`{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/dark_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png`)
- Default center: Franco da Rocha `[-23.3343, -46.6953]`, zoom `13`
- Bounds locked to: Franco da Rocha, Caieiras, Mairiporã, Francisco Morato
- `maxBoundsViscosity: 1.0` — hard limit, user cannot pan outside
- `minZoom: 12` — prevents zooming out beyond the region

## Pin Rendering

- Map pins by type with distinct colors matching Tailwind config: `flood`, `pothole`, `passable`, `robbery`
- Use custom Leaflet `divIcon` or `L.icon` for styled markers
- Attach click handlers to markers to show `PinDetails` panel

## Performance

- Use Service Worker (`public/sw.js`) for tile caching
- Avoid re-rendering the entire map — use `React.memo` on marker components
- Use `useMemo` for filtered pin arrays
- Limit heatmap data points for performance

## Geolocation

- Use `navigator.geolocation` via helper in `@/lib/helpers.ts`
- Always handle permission denied gracefully with fallback to default center
- Convert coordinates with DMS helpers when needed

## Map Events

- Handle `moveend`, `zoomend` for dynamic data loading
- Use `useMapEvents` hook from react-leaflet for event binding
